HEADWORD: Rhabdolith
<hw>Rhab"do*lith</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ra`bdos</grk> a rod + <ets>-lith</ets>.]</ety> <def>A minute
calcareous rodlike structure found both at the surface and the bottom of
the ocean; -- supposed by some to be a calcareous alga.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

